##Sharing a flight with a Wuhan Passenger: A dilemma for both sides

Lifeweek

Features an introduction to a magazine and the life he advocates.

At 9:41 am on January 29,2020, Hangzhou announced that 19 new confirmed cases had been confirmed in Hangzhou on January 28. Among them, 2 were confirmed to be from Singapore Airlines flight TR188 on January 24.
Two new cases of pneumonia were confirmed the day after the flight, which left Singapore Changi Airport for the Hangzhou Xiaoshan International Airport on Jan. 24, and the number has now risen to four. Of the 335 passengers on the flight, 116 had originally flown to Wuhan, but because the Wuhan flight was canceled, they had to return home on other flights, and Hangzhou became the destination of their collective choice.

Journalist | Ariel Xue

"Hangzhou's first. "

On the afternoon of January 24, the three members of Dai's family arrived at Changi Airport early and were unable to buy face masks. On his first day in Hangzhou, his eldest son told him that "it would be better to buy some face masks" , which he could not find in the shopping malls and several "7-11" stores near the hotel. They a family of three, until the plane landed, only from the hands of the epidemic prevention personnel to get a mask. With 4 confirmed patients on a plane with them, the entire process without protection, for the successful release of isolation, Dai Yongxin heart perturbed.

Xu and her parents are also worried. He recalled that security checks at Singapore's airport were "non-existent" , especially the lack of body temperature measurements, and appeared to be cavalier about the current outbreak.

There were four regiments on this flight, the rest of them individual passengers. One of them, Ms. Zhao, noticed that Kuhang had changed the plane's model once, and she later suspected that "it was to increase the number of 116 passengers from Wuhan to Hangzhou for temporary replacement. ". After learning of the outbreak of pneumonia in Wuhan, Singapore Airlines decided to cancel all flights to Wuhan between January 23 and February 2. Passengers on these flights could either receive a full refund or voluntarily choose to fly on other flights, flights to other mainland cities and Hong Kong, Macau, or will be indefinitely postponed.

Xu Can the family is boarding a group of people later, sitting in the back of the plane. At this point, the front of the seats have been almost full.

Five hours later, the plane landed at Hangzhou Xiaoshan International Airport on Jan. 24.

I looked at my watch, and I was 15 minutes ahead of schedule. The flight announcement caused passengers to hold off, holding down some of the passengers who were picking up their luggage as soon as the plane came to a stop. Ten minutes later, two men in Hazmat suits.

Photo courtesy of the respondents

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Boeing 787 is a wide aircraft, there are two channels, two epidemic prevention personnel from the channel began to distribute "health declaration card. ". When the three members of Dai Yongxin's family were seated in the middle row of the plane, when they were handed out, he asked, "why don't we let the flight attendants go together? " He cited the experience of normal international flight attendants issuing entry cards, i don't see why we can't do this more efficiently. The answer he got was, "stay out of it. ".

Compared with the veteran Dai Yongxin, Xu is much more "honest" , the 21-year-old university student who is fresh from all this. He thought that these are airlines and airport quarantine in extraordinary times of routine procedures, and most passengers, after filling out the form, patiently waiting to leave the cabin.

It takes about an hour and a half from the release of the form to the final release. The announcement finally said, "Wuhan passengers or passengers who have recently been to Wuhan should stay where they are, and other passengers should disembark in an orderly manner. ".

Xu Ke was sitting in the last cabin. He followed the crowd and moved little by little to the front door. The further he went, the more people he found sitting there. He thought the passengers were just unwilling to crowd, but as he passed them, he looked down and saw them, in their form, they filled out "Wuhan" in the "exit country" column. Only then did he realize that about a third of the plane was filled with Wuhan people, far more than he had suspected.

At that moment, Xu can state of mind a little collapsed, instinctively began to feel fear. On January 25, the new type of coronary pneumonia reported 1,975 confirmed cases nationwide, and other countries have been reported cases. Although people in the "new horse" , mind is every day in the mobile phone information, so many "Wuhan outbound" , more make a family feel uneasy.

Xu could not have imagined that they would be in a confined space with more than 100 people in Wuhan for up to seven hours on the last checkpoint back home. "I didn't know what I was thinking at the time, but I was ready to be infected. I was fine, but I was worried about my parents. I thought a lot of them were middle-aged and elderly. "

Airport New Year's Eve

By the time they get to the terminal, it'll be over an hour before the plane lands.

At the Water Fountain, Dai Yongxin met the flight attendants in their rows -- 11 crew members, to be quarantined along with 219 passengers. Dai recalled that during the flight, the flight attendant tried to switch places for the three of them, but then gave up. So he went up to her and asked her, "is there a passenger from Wuhan next to us? ". The flight attendant was a good-looking man from Hangzhou, but gave an ambiguous answer to her fellow-townsman's question.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The last time Dai Yongxin saw the "Wuhan Man" was shortly after he arrived at the airport lobby. He thought, after getting off the plane, there is no chance and they again intersection, did not expect to see, is two girls. When they appear in the field of vision, each side has 3"protectors" to protect the two in the middle. Ms. Zhao also saw this scene, she thought the two girls are "early twenties" , "surrounded by at least four people. They were all dressed in protective clothing, and the group appeared to be making a dramatic entrance, heading for the airport bathroom.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
After this, the plane "Wuhan People" and "non-wuhan people" completely separated. The 116 passengers who had flown to Wuhan were taken to a more enclosed area for more detailed quarantine checks. Around 3 am, a staff member arrived and told everyone that the results of the examination of 116 passengers had come out and that "seven of them were abnormal" .

The 219 passengers who originally landed in Hangzhou spent the evening in the first floor lobby of the T3 international terminal. The colder it got at night, and the people who had just returned from the tropical countries didn't have enough clothes. Xu Ke and his parents put on everything they could wear, plus blankets from the airport, but it wasn't enough, and they stayed until morning.

Around 10:00 a.m. , the Hangzhou City headquarters for the prevention and control of "coronavirus pneumonia" released an official message, "after the plane lands, two people with fever will be sent to the First People's Hospital of Xiaoshan District, the rest of the Wuhan passengers will be quarantined in the hotel at the airport, and 219 other passengers will be put under medical observation at the Party School of the Municipal Party Committee, " it said. The First People's Hospital in Xiaoshan District is the National Trib Hospital and the closest general hospital to the airport.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Dai Yongxin listened to his son brush this news on the Internet. Soon, he was confirmed on the spot by the staff. The visitor said, send everyone to the hotel first, and if there is no problem, they can go home.

After a sleepless night at the airport, the 219 passengers were finally able to move on to their next destination, which was, as the announcement put it, the Party School of the Hangzhou Municipal Party Committee. According to Dai Yongxin's observation, the convoy has seven or eight vehicles as many as five buses, and there is a lead police vehicle, every two buses between, and a police vehicle to do the interval. After about an hour, they arrived at their destination. It was midday on January 25, more than 12 hours before they landed at Xiaoshan airport.

This uneasy night is also New Year's Eve.

Quarantine initiated

The conditions at the Party School Hotel of the Hangzhou Municipal Party Committee are good. One person lives in a standard room. Every day, a food delivery robot delivers meals on a regular basis. If you need any necessities, you can make a speech on the specially organized wechat group and have someone to help you buy, including coats and coats. Because of the cold weather, isolation and observation can not turn on the heat, so each person will also be assigned a hot water bag to keep warm. What the quarantined passengers and flight attendants have to do is take their temperature at regular intervals every day, at 9:30 am and at 3 pm, to make sure they are feeling well. The rest of the time is your own, and the only way to communicate with the outside world is online.

The rest of Wuhan's passengers, quarantined at hotels near Xiaoshan airport, led a similar life for 14 days without contact with anyone except a doctor if they felt unwell.

On the first night of his isolation, Xu had a low-grade fever. He wasn't panicking, he was calm, because as he walked out the door, he knew this moment was coming. Xu Soon contacted his doctor on wechat group, with a temperature of 37.8 degrees and no other specific symptoms, which is very different from the symptoms of coronary new pneumonia. Xu's throat became inflamed, and doctors speculated that it might be just a common cold and fever. Xu can imagine also, after all, the night before at the airport frozen enough.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Although Xu could have been prepared, when the mother knew that her son had a fever, she immediately cried. The three of us live next to each other, but we don't see each other. We only have video chat every day. The Wall seems to be thousands of kilometers apart.

There are children among the 219 passengers. Ms. Zhao's daughter, who is only six, was able to share her room. For 14 long days, she coaxed her daughter's way is to tell her, "mother to take you to another place on vacation, we do a game, live here for half a month. ". The next day, the daughter said she wanted to go home, Ms. Zhao can only continue her white lie: "Not yet, to half a month, we can not lose the game. ".

If she had known the truth beforehand, she thought she would have "gotten off the plane as long as the hatch was open. ". During the quarantine, she consulted a lawyer friend and was told that the airline had a "safety and security obligation" and a "duty to inform" passengers. Another point she couldn't figure out was why the two groups of passengers, even if they were on the same plane, would sit together rather than separately? But how many of them, as Ms. Zhao hypothesized, would be willing to stay on the flight if they had been told in advance? It's an unknown quantity.

Two dilemmas

Coolair is not the only airline to make this choice.

On January 25, there were 31 passengers on flight OD688 from Malaysia to Tianjin in Wuhan. Beijing native Gao Shan told reporters that as soon as the plane landed, she saw about a dozen people on the ground wearing protective clothing. After they boarded the plane, the passengers learned that one of the original Wuhan passengers had a fever.

After waiting for four hours on the plane, an elderly male passenger in the back row was taken off the plane first, Goshen noted, but even then he was not wearing a mask and was not required to take other precautions by the epidemic prevention staff. Only some of the 31 passengers in the last rows in Wuhan were wearing masks.

The next day, Gao Shan learned from the Internet, the fever patient was diagnosed, and "for severe cases. ". On January 27, another confirmed case was found among the 31 passengers in Wuhan. That day, the Wechat Group of staff just let go, "No accident, need to be isolated for 14 days. ". No one has yet told them where they are. Gao Shan surmises from the mobile phone map that they should be quarantined in a guest house in Tianjin Flashlight Factory area.

Also on January 25, three more international flights carrying passengers destined for Wuhan landed at the Hangzhou Xiaoshan International Airport, AK1574, CA734 and MF8642, from Saba, Thailand, and Osaka, Japan, a total of 25 people from Wuhan were on the three flights, including one patient with fever. The next day, at the same time, flights from Osaka to Hangzhou continued this pattern.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo:@chocolate Turtle

The passengers on the plane had roughly the same experience. Passengers who wanted to return to Wuhan found that the flight had been canceled and had to change their tickets, land or be treated or quarantined. Instead, the non-wuhan people got on the plane without knowing it, it was only after landing that I realized I had not been safe for the last few hours.

Between them is the airline. Should the airline put two passengers on the same flight? Should the same plane be used as a minimum? Should the duty of disclosure be fulfilled? Should masks and other protective measures be provided? Passengers on all of these flights have raised these questions.

The other side of the question is how to protect the interests of Wuhan people.

On January 27, China Southern Airlines CZ380 flew from Nagoya, Japan, to Shanghai. Shanghai passengers reacted to the airport when they noticed that there were passengers from Wuhan on the same flight and did not want to fly with them on the same plane. In the end, passengers from Wuhan were able to fly back to Shanghai alone, where they were examined and treated.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
To encounter"disrelish"of Wuhan passenger, have a home hard to return after closing a city, it is difficult predicament not to be. This dilemma comes from both the rejection of compatriots, but also from some airlines "do not accept Hubei Passengers" measures, the current epidemic, leaving few options for passengers in Wuhan. As the front line of passenger transport, how to balance the interests of Hubei and non-hubei passengers is also a challenge for airlines.

In the slogan of "Treat Wuhan people well" , when there are Wuhan people around, can we treat them as well as the proposal, and how can we help them and protect ourselves? In the face of the epidemic, how to control the line of Mutual Defense between people? HOW TO BALANCE EPIDEMIC BORDERS AND HUMANITARIAN CONCERNS? Facing the coming "rework tide" , this is both to the individual, but also to the society put forward the bigger problem.

(Dai Yongxin, Xu Ke and Gao Shan are aliases, and Intern reporter Zhang Jiajing is helpful.)
